WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.958
Support Admin Watch on
kissasia.cam or kisskh.org

00:10.000 --> 00:13.083
[Betty] I know
we're all hurting right now.

00:14.125 --> 00:16.958
But our priority has to be to maintain

00:17.000 --> 00:18.833
the security of this Vault.

00:18.875 --> 00:20.125
[Norm] They don't want to find Dad.

00:20.250 --> 00:21.958
If they did,
they wouldn't get to be in charge.

00:22.041 --> 00:23.625
[Lucy] I'm bringing him home.

00:25.375 --> 00:26.458
Hit him again!

00:26.541 --> 00:27.416
[grunts]

00:28.791 --> 00:31.166
-[roaring]
-[Titus] Oh! Shoot it!

00:33.041 --> 00:35.750
You stupid motherfucker,
you know this is all your fault.

00:35.791 --> 00:37.541
They'll kill you for this.

00:37.666 --> 00:39.291
[Maximus] Not if I bring back the target.

00:39.375 --> 00:42.083
[Wilzig] You can change the future

00:42.166 --> 00:46.000
if you can bring me to Moldaver.

00:46.958 --> 00:48.291
Just my head.

00:48.833 --> 00:51.875
You are a vault dweller,

00:51.958 --> 00:53.750
but if you're going to survive,

00:53.833 --> 00:55.708
you need to start acting
like a surface dweller.

00:57.000 --> 00:58.291
Question is,

00:58.375 --> 01:00.916
will you still want the same things...

01:04.000 --> 01:08.000
...when you have become
a different animal altogether?

01:21.375 --> 01:23.375
[western music playing]

01:29.041 --> 01:31.041
[man grunting]

01:34.750 --> 01:36.750
♪ ♪

01:42.166 --> 01:44.416
[villain] Please, sir.

01:44.500 --> 01:47.458
Please, sir, please.

01:50.500 --> 01:52.583
There's an old Mexican eulogy.

01:52.666 --> 01:55.666
Feo fuerte y formal.

01:55.750 --> 01:58.916
Means he was ugly, strong,

01:59.000 --> 02:00.958
and had dignity.

02:01.041 --> 02:02.916
Well, Joey,

02:03.000 --> 02:06.708
I'll give you
two out of three on that front.

02:08.250 --> 02:10.250
[whimpering]

02:21.458 --> 02:23.500
Do I really have to kill him?

02:23.583 --> 02:26.416
-[director] Cut.
-[bell rings]

02:29.208 --> 02:31.750
Emil, can you come over here?
I got to talk to you for a second.

02:31.833 --> 02:33.083
Yeah, here you go.

02:33.166 --> 02:35.208
That was a hell of a day, Jorge.
That was a great scene.

02:35.291 --> 02:38.166
Listen, I got to talk to you
about these, these new pages, you know?

02:38.250 --> 02:40.458
I mean, I-I'm the sheriff, right?

02:40.541 --> 02:42.750
Well, why can't I just arrest the guy
like I normally do?

02:42.833 --> 02:45.750
-That's what I do. All right.
-The au… the audience, Coop, yeah?

02:45.833 --> 02:47.625
They already know you're a good man.

02:47.708 --> 02:49.875
They want to see that even a good man

02:49.958 --> 02:52.375
-as yourself can be driven
too far sometimes.
-Yeah, I understand that.

02:52.458 --> 02:54.500
But that's not really my thing,
you know, Emil, that's not what I do.

02:54.583 --> 02:56.958
I mean, is Bob,
is Bob around here anywhere?

02:57.041 --> 02:59.291
-Bob's been fired, Coop.
-What?

02:59.375 --> 03:01.291
Studio fired him.

03:01.375 --> 03:02.916
Why?

03:03.000 --> 03:04.958
See, turns out...

03:05.041 --> 03:07.375
Bob's a bit of a communist.

03:07.458 --> 03:09.375
-A communist? Cadillac Bob?
-Yeah.

03:09.458 --> 03:11.166
Cadillac Bob! The very one.

03:11.250 --> 03:13.375
-Well, what a shame,
he was such a great writer.
-Terrible shame.

03:13.458 --> 03:15.750
One of the best, but he had to go.

03:15.833 --> 03:18.083
Which is why this movie is so important.

03:18.166 --> 03:20.166
-Right.
-You see, it's a new kind of western.

03:20.250 --> 03:23.541
The power of the individual
when the chips are down.

03:23.625 --> 03:25.875
The new America,
it's why I'm telling you, so...

03:25.958 --> 03:28.916
that's why it'd be
really great if you could just…

03:29.000 --> 03:31.708
shoot Jorge in the fucking head, yeah?

03:31.791 --> 03:34.166
-Please. 'Cause out here...
-Right.

03:34.250 --> 03:38.333
...it's just you, your gun,
and your personal code bringing order

03:38.416 --> 03:40.833
-to the Wild Wild West!
-Yeah. Uh, hey, let's, uh,

03:40.916 --> 03:42.916
let's pick this up after lunch, all right?

03:48.000 --> 03:51.166
You gonna save any of
that grape taffy for the rest of us?

03:51.250 --> 03:53.958
It's not grape. It's lavender.

03:55.000 --> 03:56.750
Well, if you like the taste of lavender,

03:56.833 --> 03:58.500
why not just drink a bottle of perfume?

03:59.750 --> 04:02.875
You know, a lot of people like
to write it off as some old lady flavor,

04:02.958 --> 04:05.500
but it's subtle.

04:05.583 --> 04:07.791
Flirtatious.

04:07.875 --> 04:11.000
Tastes like someone touching you
for the first time.

04:12.708 --> 04:15.250
Well, may I?

04:20.957 --> 04:22.957
Mm.

04:28.541 --> 04:31.791
-Um, that's the worst thing...
-[laughs]

04:31.875 --> 04:34.166
...I've ever put in my mouth.

04:34.250 --> 04:36.416
-That's horrible.
-Taffy?

04:36.500 --> 04:39.625
Um, you got to ask your mother.

04:39.707 --> 04:42.207
-Please, Mommy?
-Sure, sweetheart.

04:42.291 --> 04:44.416
Oh, wow.

04:44.500 --> 04:46.457
Unbelievable. Hey.

04:46.541 --> 04:47.916
Mm.

04:48.000 --> 04:49.500
Oh, sorry, makeup.

04:55.707 --> 04:58.291
Sorry, lipstick.

04:58.375 --> 05:00.208
I'll take it.

05:00.291 --> 05:01.958
-Okay, we should get going.
-All right.

05:02.041 --> 05:03.708
Photographer's ready and waiting.

05:03.791 --> 05:05.333
Okay, what is this?

05:05.416 --> 05:08.541
A bit of a costume change
for you, Mr. Howard.

05:08.625 --> 05:10.625
Ah, okay.

05:12.166 --> 05:14.791
Oh, look at that.

05:16.791 --> 05:20.207
They even made it in your color.

05:20.291 --> 05:22.332
Let's see if it fits.

05:22.416 --> 05:24.291
Okay, Janey.

05:24.375 --> 05:26.707
Let's go.

05:26.791 --> 05:28.416
Come on, here. Come here.

05:28.500 --> 05:30.500
[conversing indistinctly]

05:31.750 --> 05:33.750
[intriguing music playing]

05:40.000 --> 05:42.166
♪ ♪

05:56.750 --> 05:58.791
[coughs]

06:03.875 --> 06:05.875
[coughing]

06:21.082 --> 06:22.082
[spits]

06:22.166 --> 06:23.416
[coughs]

06:29.707 --> 06:31.832
[coughs]

06:31.916 --> 06:33.957
[wheezes]

06:36.000 --> 06:38.000
[suspenseful music playing]

06:41.750 --> 06:43.041
[CX404 whimpers]

06:46.875 --> 06:49.457
Come on, let's go find the rest of him.

06:49.541 --> 06:51.332
[clucking tongue]

06:52.416 --> 06:54.041
[CX404 barks]

06:56.791 --> 06:58.375
[barks]

07:05.791 --> 07:07.791
♪ ♪

07:14.333 --> 07:16.832
[♪ The Ink Spots: "Maybe"]

07:24.791 --> 07:29.666
♪ Maybe ♪

07:29.750 --> 07:34.916
♪ You'll think of me ♪

07:35.000 --> 07:38.875
♪ When you are all ♪

07:38.957 --> 07:42.875
♪ Alone ♪

07:44.875 --> 07:47.832
♪ Maybe ♪

07:47.916 --> 07:52.416
♪ The one who is waiting ♪

07:52.500 --> 07:55.625
♪ For you ♪

07:55.707 --> 08:00.166
♪ Will prove untrue ♪

08:00.250 --> 08:02.958
♪ Then what will ♪

08:03.041 --> 08:06.291
♪ You do? ♪

08:06.375 --> 08:11.416
♪ Maybe ♪

08:11.500 --> 08:15.833
♪ You'll sit and sigh...

08:15.916 --> 08:17.707
All right.

08:17.791 --> 08:21.207
What is so special about you?

08:21.291 --> 08:24.332
♪ Were near…

08:24.416 --> 08:25.375
Ow!

08:27.041 --> 08:30.041
♪ Maybe ♪

08:30.125 --> 08:31.707
♪ You'll…

08:31.791 --> 08:33.665
Ow!

08:33.750 --> 08:36.665
Okay, okay.

08:36.750 --> 08:38.665
Keep your secrets, sir.

08:38.750 --> 08:40.750
♪ Are all...

08:40.832 --> 08:42.832
Just in case.

08:48.540 --> 08:50.625
To keep you extra safe.

08:50.708 --> 08:55.958
♪ Who is waiting for you...

08:56.040 --> 08:57.583
Hmm.

08:57.665 --> 09:00.416
♪ Will prove untrue...

09:00.500 --> 09:01.458
Huh.

09:01.541 --> 09:05.500
♪ Then what will I do? ♪

09:06.791 --> 09:08.625
There.

09:08.708 --> 09:11.416
Snug as a bug. [chuckles]

09:13.583 --> 09:15.583
[sighs]

09:15.666 --> 09:17.416
[clears throat]

09:18.458 --> 09:21.958
♪ Wishing that I ♪

09:22.041 --> 09:25.166
♪ Were near ♪

09:25.250 --> 09:27.791
♪ Then ♪

09:27.875 --> 09:30.125
♪ Maybe...

09:30.208 --> 09:32.665
Boy, that knight
really was something, huh?

09:32.750 --> 09:35.375
♪ Come back...

09:35.458 --> 09:37.833
I wonder who he was?

09:38.915 --> 09:43.665
♪ And maybe ♪

09:43.750 --> 09:45.958
♪ I'll say ♪

09:46.040 --> 09:50.500
♪ Maybe ♪♪

10:00.083 --> 10:02.208
[chickens clucking]

10:02.291 --> 10:03.916
[comms officer] Knight Titus.

10:08.666 --> 10:10.750
Knight Titus.

10:17.500 --> 10:19.750
Knight Titus!

10:21.958 --> 10:24.000
[deeper voice] This is Knight Titus.

10:24.083 --> 10:26.041
Over.

10:26.125 --> 10:27.541
This is Petty Officer Shortsight.

10:27.625 --> 10:29.166
You missed your check-in.

10:32.458 --> 10:35.415
We were attacked, uh,

10:35.500 --> 10:37.583
by an abomination.

10:37.665 --> 10:39.458
My squire, he fell in battle.

10:39.540 --> 10:41.915
He died with honor.

10:42.000 --> 10:44.000
And glory.

10:45.708 --> 10:48.583
Copy that. We'll get you
a replacement squire right away.

10:48.665 --> 10:51.165
No! No, I'm okay.

10:51.250 --> 10:53.375
-All good here.
-It's not a problem.

10:53.458 --> 10:55.290
We got plenty of squires.

10:55.375 --> 10:56.333
No.

11:06.375 --> 11:07.916
Yeah, uh...

11:08.000 --> 11:10.291
I'll be right back.

11:10.375 --> 11:12.833
[suspenseful music plays]

11:18.958 --> 11:20.958
[indistinct chatter]

11:42.290 --> 11:43.708
[metallic echo] I can fix it.

11:43.790 --> 11:46.083
Cost you five caps.

11:46.165 --> 11:49.040
[intense music playing]

11:50.165 --> 11:52.540
[caps jingling]

11:54.708 --> 11:57.000
Uh, could you do it for four?

12:01.000 --> 12:02.583
No.

12:18.625 --> 12:21.125
[intriguing music playing]

12:26.750 --> 12:28.916
It's extra if you do it fast.

12:33.165 --> 12:34.750
Thanks.

12:40.958 --> 12:43.415
♪ ♪

12:48.125 --> 12:50.125
[indistinct chatter]

12:56.708 --> 12:58.333
Fack! [grunts]

13:02.375 --> 13:04.750
Step away from the armor.

13:06.875 --> 13:09.541
[laughing]

13:09.625 --> 13:11.666
Kick the shit out of him.

13:14.291 --> 13:16.208
[grunting]

13:39.500 --> 13:41.500
Finders keepers.

13:43.415 --> 13:44.708
Milord.

13:51.083 --> 13:52.875
[laughs]

14:03.750 --> 14:06.416
Let's get her open... Open it, open it!

14:06.500 --> 14:09.041
What are you doing, you fuckin' moron?!

14:09.125 --> 14:11.416
It's righty-tighty, lefty-loosey.

14:17.000 --> 14:19.000
[Tom laughs]

14:21.833 --> 14:24.583
[energetic music playing]

14:36.333 --> 14:38.625
[Tom] Ah-ha! Fuck with me now!

14:40.333 --> 14:42.250
-[laughter]
-[chatter]

14:54.875 --> 14:56.875
[♪ Johnny Cash: "So Doggone Lonesome"]

15:06.958 --> 15:10.958
♪ I do my best to hide
this lowdown feeling ♪

15:11.041 --> 15:15.708
♪ I try to make believe
there's nothing wrong ♪

15:15.791 --> 15:19.500
♪ But they're always asking me
about you, darling ♪

15:20.958 --> 15:23.916
♪ And it hurts me so
to tell 'em that you're gone ♪

15:24.000 --> 15:25.625
[grunting]

15:25.708 --> 15:29.041
-♪ If they ask me,
I guess I'd be denying...
-Fuck him up! [laughs]

15:29.125 --> 15:31.291
Whoo! My fuckin' armor!

15:31.375 --> 15:33.583
[grunting]

15:39.833 --> 15:42.165
Fuck him up. Fuck him up. [laughs]

15:46.083 --> 15:47.290
[gasps]

15:47.375 --> 15:48.875
[grunts]

15:54.165 --> 15:56.333
[screaming]

16:04.250 --> 16:06.250
[grunts]

16:11.166 --> 16:13.750
[nearby rumbling]

16:21.916 --> 16:24.833
No! No, no, no, no, no, no... [grunts]

16:35.665 --> 16:37.625
[automated voice] No cause
for alarm, citizens.

16:37.708 --> 16:39.708
This is a Brotherhood delivery.

16:45.625 --> 16:48.290
No cause for alarm, citizens…

16:50.290 --> 16:53.040
[intense music playing]

16:53.915 --> 16:55.665
[grunts]

17:24.790 --> 17:26.708
Knight Titus.

17:26.790 --> 17:28.750
I am Thaddeus.

17:30.208 --> 17:32.041
And I am honored to be in your charge.

17:34.291 --> 17:38.375
I vow to protect and serve you
however you deem fit.

17:41.833 --> 17:43.541
My Lord,

17:43.625 --> 17:45.916
have I said something wrong?

17:50.958 --> 17:52.583
I do not know what I have done to offend,

17:52.666 --> 17:54.250
but I beg for mercy!

17:54.333 --> 17:56.625
Please. Please.

17:56.708 --> 17:58.333
Please, please...

17:59.333 --> 18:00.500
Knight Titus!

18:00.583 --> 18:03.291
Please! I-I'll do anything!

18:03.375 --> 18:04.583
[chuckles]

18:04.666 --> 18:06.625
[distorted] Arise, my squire.

18:08.375 --> 18:10.250
And clean this.

18:13.375 --> 18:15.541
Of course, Knight Titus.

18:19.291 --> 18:21.750
I also bring new orders
from the Elder Cleric.

18:21.833 --> 18:24.166
Uh, which I humbly relay.

18:25.250 --> 18:27.375
Mm.

18:27.458 --> 18:30.125
We're not the only ones in search
of this remnant from the old world.

18:30.208 --> 18:32.583
The Elder Cleric says

18:32.666 --> 18:34.666
whoever gets the target

18:34.750 --> 18:36.583
will control the Wasteland.

18:36.666 --> 18:38.291
And, uh...

18:38.375 --> 18:40.708
we are to kill whomever stands in our way.

18:46.166 --> 18:48.166
[Maximus] Understood.

18:58.375 --> 19:00.375
[gentle music playing]

19:14.000 --> 19:16.000
[chuckles softly]

19:38.375 --> 19:40.375
♪ ♪

20:00.916 --> 20:03.333
You like grass?

20:13.750 --> 20:14.958
Hi.

20:15.041 --> 20:17.041
[low growling]

20:27.875 --> 20:29.916
-[creature roars]
-[fawn screeches]

20:38.083 --> 20:40.291
[low growl]

20:40.375 --> 20:43.125
[roars]

20:52.958 --> 20:55.208
[water splashes]

21:07.166 --> 21:08.916
[panting]

21:16.208 --> 21:19.083
[rad meter peaking]

21:29.166 --> 21:31.166
[gun cocks]

21:41.916 --> 21:43.458
Huh.

21:43.541 --> 21:45.500
[exhales]

21:45.583 --> 21:47.208
Hello again.

21:50.708 --> 21:52.791
Where is it?

21:52.875 --> 21:55.000
-The head.
-[whimpering]

21:59.125 --> 22:00.541
[CX404 barks]

22:06.083 --> 22:07.083
[exhales]

22:07.166 --> 22:08.666
No.

22:08.750 --> 22:10.833
Okay, okay, I-I don't know

22:10.916 --> 22:13.458
where it is, okay? I lost it.

22:15.750 --> 22:17.750
I lost it.

22:17.833 --> 22:19.625
[laughs]

22:20.666 --> 22:22.291
Huh.

22:32.333 --> 22:34.583
Huh.

22:36.583 --> 22:39.041
A Gulper got it, huh?

22:44.375 --> 22:48.958
-[♪ The Ink Spots: "We'll Meet Again"]
-♪ We'll meet again ♪

22:49.041 --> 22:50.625
♪ Don't know where...

22:50.708 --> 22:51.750
[sobbing in distance]

22:51.833 --> 22:54.666
♪ Don't know when ♪

22:54.750 --> 22:58.875
♪ But I know we'll meet again ♪

22:58.958 --> 23:02.375
♪ Some sunny day...

23:02.458 --> 23:04.166
You okay?

23:04.250 --> 23:07.291
Yeah. I'm being reassigned.

23:07.375 --> 23:09.958
The whole "opening the Vault door
for Lucy" thing

23:10.041 --> 23:12.583
didn't sit too well
with the Council, so...

23:12.666 --> 23:15.791
I guess I'm not Gate-Keeper anymore.

23:17.291 --> 23:18.583
It's not a big deal.

23:18.666 --> 23:21.458
♪ Till the blue skies
drive the dark clouds...

23:21.541 --> 23:24.625
I'm just not really sure
who I even am anymore.

23:27.541 --> 23:29.250
Sorry, I...

23:29.333 --> 23:31.083
♪ Meet again...

23:31.166 --> 23:32.333
Mm.

23:32.416 --> 23:34.916
♪ Don't know where ♪

23:35.000 --> 23:37.333
♪ Don't know when...

23:37.416 --> 23:39.583
[Chet crying]

23:39.666 --> 23:42.041
Norman, you're next.

23:42.125 --> 23:45.791
♪ Some sunny day ♪♪

23:48.458 --> 23:51.458
[door slides shut]

23:54.250 --> 23:55.500
You know why you're in here?

23:55.583 --> 23:57.041
'Cause I helped my sister
escape the Vault.

23:57.125 --> 24:00.041
Escape? You and Chet put your sister
in incredible danger

24:00.125 --> 24:01.791
by helping her out that Vault door.

24:01.875 --> 24:03.916
-The rad levels up there alone--
-Worse,

24:04.000 --> 24:05.916
you could've gotten us all killed.

24:06.000 --> 24:08.375
What do you think started all this?

24:08.458 --> 24:10.291
These Vaults are impenetrable.

24:10.375 --> 24:12.583
Meaning those raiders
could only have gotten into Vault 32

24:12.666 --> 24:16.125
because some bonehead
opened the door to the surface.

24:16.208 --> 24:19.666
A single bad decision
that put everyone at risk.

24:19.750 --> 24:24.958
Not just Vault 32, but 33 and 31 as well.

24:25.041 --> 24:28.666
I've telegrammed with the Overseer
at Vault 31.

24:28.750 --> 24:31.250
Thank goodness they're unscathed.

24:31.333 --> 24:35.333
But you could've destroyed
the last vestiges of civilization.

24:35.416 --> 24:36.791
It was Lucy's idea.

24:36.875 --> 24:38.708
[Woody] And you didn't think
to at least try and stop her?

24:38.791 --> 24:39.750
No.

24:40.791 --> 24:42.416
What are we gonna do with you?

24:43.625 --> 24:45.625
Punish me with a demotion, I guess.

24:45.708 --> 24:47.125
[sighs]

24:48.833 --> 24:52.208
You've worked janitorial.
You've done kitchen duty.

24:52.291 --> 24:55.833
Are you aware that, at every job
you've been assigned to,

24:55.916 --> 24:59.083
your performance review has been
"lacks enthusiasm"?

25:00.416 --> 25:02.083
No, but that sounds accurate.

25:03.541 --> 25:06.500
You're currently working with Computers

25:06.583 --> 25:08.750
and Information Maintenance.

25:08.833 --> 25:10.041
How do you like that?

25:11.250 --> 25:12.916
I lack enthusiasm.

25:13.958 --> 25:15.083
Uh-huh.

25:16.708 --> 25:18.916
It's a predicament, isn't it?

25:19.000 --> 25:22.708
How do you demote someone who equally
dislikes every job he's ever worked?

25:23.875 --> 25:25.166
I suppose it is.

25:25.250 --> 25:28.333
I'm just glad to hear that we punish
people down here for breaking the rules.

25:28.416 --> 25:31.083
Is that just for vault dwellers,
or for people who come down here

25:31.166 --> 25:33.000
and murder vault dwellers?

25:33.083 --> 25:35.541
[tense music playing]

25:40.125 --> 25:43.208
Now that I think of it,

25:43.291 --> 25:45.958
we've got a job for you after all.

25:50.333 --> 25:52.916
-[♪ LaVern Baker: "Tweedlee Dee"]
-♪ Tweedlee dee, tweedlee dee ♪

25:53.000 --> 25:54.166
♪ Tweedlee dee...

25:54.250 --> 25:56.291
[buzzer sounds]

25:56.375 --> 25:59.625
♪ Tweedlee tweedlee tweedlee dee ♪

26:01.916 --> 26:06.333
♪ I'm as happy as can be...

26:07.583 --> 26:08.958
Rise and shine, everyone.

26:09.041 --> 26:10.125
Ooh.

26:10.208 --> 26:12.375
[Marianne] Your catered snackables
have arrived.

26:14.041 --> 26:17.125
-[prisoner] Come on. Hurry up.
-[Marianne] And you're welcome.

26:20.916 --> 26:23.083
-[prisoner shouts]
-Okay.

26:23.166 --> 26:25.875
-There is a utensil--
-[prisoner] I'm gonna eat
your fucking heart!

26:25.958 --> 26:30.041
♪ Tweedlee, tweedlee, tweedlee dot ♪

26:31.291 --> 26:32.250
[prisoner growls]

26:32.333 --> 26:36.375
-♪ Tweedlee dee, tweedlee dee ♪
-I'll break your fucking head open!

26:36.458 --> 26:37.875
Whoo!

26:37.958 --> 26:42.125
♪ Give it up, give it up,
give your love to me ♪♪

26:47.208 --> 26:48.916
[Thaddeus] I don't see any apples, sir.

26:49.000 --> 26:51.500
[Maximus] [distorted] Then climb higher.

26:51.583 --> 26:54.583
It-it might not be an apple tree.

26:54.666 --> 26:55.916
Also, it's uh...

26:56.000 --> 26:59.166
I think, uh, it's dead.

26:59.250 --> 27:00.750
[Maximus] Keep looking.

27:00.833 --> 27:02.791
On my honor, sir, I will find you--

27:02.875 --> 27:04.416
Fuck!

27:04.500 --> 27:06.500
[groaning]

27:09.791 --> 27:13.166
-[Maximus chuckles]
-Uh, uh, sorry. Apologies, sir.

27:13.250 --> 27:15.333
I know you wanted an apple.

27:15.416 --> 27:20.041
Uh, uh, I have some-some rations
if you're hungry.

27:20.125 --> 27:21.208
I'm not hungry anymore.

27:21.291 --> 27:24.250
Uh, okay, yeah. Whatever you want.

27:24.333 --> 27:26.833
Uh, you're the sir.

27:29.291 --> 27:31.791
I have an artifact to retrieve. Let's go.

27:31.875 --> 27:34.083
[groans] Okay.

27:34.166 --> 27:36.041
Uh, if we find the target,

27:36.125 --> 27:37.833
we should repair your radio

27:37.916 --> 27:40.666
so we can ask the Brotherhood
to send reinforcements.

27:42.041 --> 27:44.458
I will retrieve it myself.

27:44.541 --> 27:46.208
Understood. Understood.

27:46.291 --> 27:48.208
I never doubted your ability to do so.

27:55.208 --> 27:57.333
[straining]

27:57.416 --> 28:00.750
The guy from the Enclave,
the guy everybody's looking for,

28:00.833 --> 28:02.000
you saw him?

28:02.083 --> 28:04.458
I did. He left with a girl.

28:04.541 --> 28:06.708
-A woman.
-How'd they get away?

28:06.791 --> 28:10.041
I was waylaid. A ghoul intervened.

28:10.125 --> 28:13.583
A ghoul?! Huh.
Those things are scary as shit.

28:13.666 --> 28:15.416
I bet you just killed it on sight,
no questions asked.

28:15.500 --> 28:16.875
"Oh, you're a ghoul?

28:16.958 --> 28:19.291
-You're a dead ghoul."
-No.

28:19.375 --> 28:22.333
If we find the ghoul, we find the target.

28:22.416 --> 28:24.291
You left the ghoul alive?

28:26.041 --> 28:27.291
Great idea, sir.

28:27.375 --> 28:30.000
All wastelanders leave radiation trails.

28:30.083 --> 28:33.083
By allowing the ghoul to live,
you've made it possible

28:33.166 --> 28:36.666
to trace the whereabouts of the…
of the target.

28:38.250 --> 28:42.083
Yes, right. I know that.

28:42.166 --> 28:43.333
[rad meter peaking rapidly]

28:43.416 --> 28:45.208
I got a trail.

28:45.291 --> 28:47.458
Yeah. Well done, sir.

28:47.541 --> 28:50.583
This way. Glory awaits!

28:53.125 --> 28:54.791
Oh, yes.

28:54.875 --> 28:56.875
[dramatic music playing]

29:04.458 --> 29:05.916
Think this was him?

29:07.458 --> 29:09.125
[Maximus] Hard to tell.

29:09.208 --> 29:11.458
Show me the illustration.

29:14.583 --> 29:17.041
Oh, yeah.

29:17.125 --> 29:19.041
Yeah, that-that's definitely him.

29:19.125 --> 29:21.791
Think we should, uh,
bring the body back with us?

29:21.875 --> 29:23.416
No.

29:23.500 --> 29:25.875
If they left the body,
it must be worthless.

29:25.958 --> 29:28.750
His head is what's valuable.
We need to find it.

29:28.833 --> 29:30.333
[Thaddeus] Oh, yeah, smart.

29:30.416 --> 29:31.750
Who do you think did this,
the girl or the ghoul?

29:31.833 --> 29:35.291
The ghoul. Definitely.

29:35.375 --> 29:36.541
Ghouls.

29:36.625 --> 29:40.083
One day the Brotherhood's gonna eradicate
every last one of those freaks.

29:40.166 --> 29:43.458
Stuff like this is never
gonna happen again.

29:44.791 --> 29:48.791
Okay, so I think that the ghoul probably

29:48.875 --> 29:51.958
should be, I think, uh, well...

29:52.041 --> 29:54.916
Yeah, definitely this, um--

29:56.791 --> 29:59.958
Yeah, that way.
Definitely-- definitely that way.

30:00.041 --> 30:02.041
There's tracks. [chuckles]

30:03.791 --> 30:05.791
[intriguing music playing]

30:12.541 --> 30:14.458
[CX404 barking in distance]

30:18.458 --> 30:20.166
Stop, please!

30:21.750 --> 30:23.875
My dad, he's an Overseer.

30:23.958 --> 30:26.833
He-he got taken by raiders,
and I need that head to get him back.

30:26.916 --> 30:29.666
If you help me find him,
he'll do whatever you want.

30:29.750 --> 30:30.708
[cries out]

30:32.333 --> 30:33.750
[muffled shouts]

30:37.666 --> 30:40.375
[CX404 continues barking]

30:44.250 --> 30:47.208
[coughing, gasping]

30:47.291 --> 30:49.791
Stop. Stop!

30:49.875 --> 30:51.666
Torture is wrong.

30:51.750 --> 30:53.083
[Lucy coughs]

30:53.166 --> 30:56.750
You know, they used to do these things

30:56.833 --> 30:59.416
called "studies."

30:59.500 --> 31:01.208
Why, you couldn't open a newspaper

31:01.291 --> 31:04.000
without reading about
one study or another.

31:04.083 --> 31:06.500
-[rad meter peaking rapidly]
-Anyway, this one particular study
came out,

31:06.583 --> 31:11.375
and it said that torturing a person
don't do shit.

31:11.458 --> 31:13.041
[Lucy screams]

31:13.125 --> 31:14.958
[muffled groans]

31:21.250 --> 31:23.708
[gasping and gagging]

31:25.541 --> 31:27.291
It made sense.

31:27.375 --> 31:29.416
I mean, a man hurts me,

31:29.500 --> 31:31.750
I wouldn't want to do him any favors.

31:31.833 --> 31:35.625
And yet the practice of torture
failed to vanish from this earth.

31:35.708 --> 31:39.250
In fact, as time marched on,

31:39.333 --> 31:44.416
I've personally noticed
a decided uptick...

31:45.583 --> 31:47.833
...in the amount of torture
being doled out across the board.

31:47.916 --> 31:50.875
Sir, please, I need the head.

31:50.958 --> 31:53.625
It's the only way
I can get my father back.

31:53.708 --> 31:55.958
My point is...

31:56.041 --> 32:00.583
if you ask me, them studies,
they was right.

32:00.666 --> 32:03.125
Torturing a person don't do shit.

32:03.208 --> 32:06.666
Then why… why are you doing this?

32:06.750 --> 32:09.666
Well, I ain't torturing you, sweetheart.

32:10.708 --> 32:12.625
I'm using you as bait.

32:15.958 --> 32:17.666
[CX404 barking]

32:17.750 --> 32:19.958
[whistles]

32:20.041 --> 32:22.125
[whistling]

32:23.000 --> 32:23.958
Nice.

32:24.041 --> 32:26.291
[ominous music playing]

32:35.125 --> 32:36.416
[cries out]

32:39.083 --> 32:40.583
[cries out]

32:42.583 --> 32:44.583
[jarring music playing]

32:57.208 --> 32:58.416
[barking]

33:00.875 --> 33:03.750
[creature growling]

33:13.833 --> 33:16.000
[Lucy grunting]

33:44.500 --> 33:46.375
[barking]

33:48.000 --> 33:51.416
[Gulper screaming]

33:51.500 --> 33:53.458
[CX404 barking]

33:53.541 --> 33:55.250
Ah.

33:55.333 --> 33:57.000
[inhales]

33:57.083 --> 33:58.958
[sighs sharply]

33:59.041 --> 34:00.708
[Lucy panting]

34:15.125 --> 34:16.916
Motherfucker!

34:17.916 --> 34:21.583
Oh, I'm sorry, I should have
just let you use me as bait

34:21.666 --> 34:23.250
in a poison river?!

34:27.875 --> 34:28.958
Fuck!

34:29.041 --> 34:30.916
[Lucy] You can't treat people like this.

34:31.000 --> 34:32.583
Yeah? Why's that?

34:34.375 --> 34:36.125
Because of the golden rule.

34:37.583 --> 34:41.041
"Do unto others as you would have
done unto you."

34:43.333 --> 34:45.916
Those Gulpers digest real slow.

34:46.000 --> 34:47.833
You got time.

34:56.625 --> 34:58.208
No. No, no, no.

34:58.291 --> 34:59.416
No. Stop.

34:59.500 --> 35:01.375
[grunting]

35:03.750 --> 35:05.541
Where are we going?

35:05.625 --> 35:06.833
What about the head?

35:06.916 --> 35:08.333
I need the head to get my dad back.

35:08.416 --> 35:10.583
Yeah, well, the Wasteland's got
its own golden rule.

35:10.666 --> 35:11.666
Oh? What's that?

35:11.750 --> 35:15.250
Thou shalt get sidetracked by bullshit
every goddamn time.

35:15.333 --> 35:16.916
[barking]

35:17.000 --> 35:19.333
-What about the dog?
-He ain't mine.

35:30.666 --> 35:33.041
[gentle music playing]

35:34.125 --> 35:37.166
Sorry, I've been derelict
in my duties here.

35:37.250 --> 35:38.166
[grunts]

35:39.958 --> 35:41.208
[distorted] What are you doing?

35:41.291 --> 35:44.875
Uh, just refilling your water bag
so you can stay hydrated.

35:46.500 --> 35:47.666
Right.

35:50.916 --> 35:55.166
Uh, it might be faster if you sit down.

35:59.125 --> 36:01.875
Bet you, uh, seen some things, huh?

36:01.958 --> 36:03.791
Being a knight.

36:03.875 --> 36:05.458
I've seen some things.

36:05.541 --> 36:08.041
I grew up working on a fly farm.

36:08.125 --> 36:10.166
I was a shitter, so they'd feed us,

36:10.250 --> 36:13.125
and then they'd feed our shit
to the flies.

36:13.208 --> 36:15.833
Mulch 'em up and sell it as protein.

36:15.916 --> 36:17.458
Anyway, that's why I'm so fat.

36:21.291 --> 36:24.375
So, your, uh, former squire,

36:24.458 --> 36:26.166
how did he die?

36:27.208 --> 36:29.125
You knew him?

36:29.208 --> 36:31.250
Yeah, I-- I did.

36:31.333 --> 36:32.833
Say something about him.

36:32.916 --> 36:36.000
Well, he, uh, he was a good guy.

36:38.250 --> 36:40.458
Say something negative about him.

36:40.541 --> 36:45.250
Well, uh, he-he's dead.
I don't know, it feels weird.

36:45.333 --> 36:48.416
-An order, my squire.
-Okay.

36:48.500 --> 36:51.375
Uh, to be honest,

36:51.458 --> 36:55.291
me and the other guys used
to be pretty hard on him.

36:55.375 --> 36:57.583
Like, regularly beat the shit out of him.

36:57.666 --> 36:59.541
It wasn't personal, you know.

36:59.625 --> 37:01.083
It's just...

37:02.333 --> 37:05.000
...well, you know, people at the base,

37:05.083 --> 37:08.458
they used to beat the shit out of me
all the time.

37:09.958 --> 37:14.666
This shipment of new recruits came in,
and, uh, one of them was Maximus.

37:14.750 --> 37:16.291
So I had this funny idea,

37:16.375 --> 37:18.708
what if we beat the shit
out of that guy instead?

37:18.791 --> 37:20.583
And it worked.

37:20.666 --> 37:24.083
Yeah, I was really popular. It was great.

37:24.166 --> 37:27.125
I just wish he'd lived long enough to find
someone else to beat up, you know?

37:27.208 --> 37:29.333
Only seems fair.

37:29.416 --> 37:31.875
I realize that, uh,
people die all the time.

37:31.958 --> 37:34.458
It's the law of the Wasteland,
so who cares, right?

37:35.666 --> 37:39.458
But still, uh, I feel bad.

37:41.333 --> 37:43.458
Don't feel bad.

37:43.541 --> 37:47.750
It's like you said,
it's the law of the Wasteland.

37:49.791 --> 37:52.541
Let's go. We're losing daylight.

37:52.625 --> 37:54.625
Yeah.

37:56.125 --> 37:58.416
[melancholy music playing]

38:02.791 --> 38:04.666
[Thaddeus] Coming!

38:09.875 --> 38:12.250
[Woody] We can judge a person,
and a society,

38:12.333 --> 38:13.875
by how they treat their enemy.

38:13.958 --> 38:17.416
And here we are
with 16 highly-violent individuals

38:17.500 --> 38:21.291
incarcerated in our temporarily
repurposed reading room.

38:21.375 --> 38:24.125
It's an ethical dilemma
like nothing we've dealt with before.

38:24.208 --> 38:26.958
[Reg] Personally, I'd say
it's more of an ethical opportunity

38:27.041 --> 38:30.583
to demonstrate to the surface dwellers,
and to each other,

38:30.666 --> 38:34.166
what we mean when we say
we're going to build a better world.

38:34.250 --> 38:36.750
Thanks, Reg.
That is a positive spin to put on it.

38:36.833 --> 38:38.875
-[microphone squeaks]
-It's not a positive spin for me.

38:38.958 --> 38:40.875
It's the goshdarn truth!

38:40.958 --> 38:43.875
Okay, well, uh, the fact remains

38:43.958 --> 38:46.416
we need to decide
what to do with these prisoners.

38:46.500 --> 38:49.875
And that is a decision
that we need to make as a collective.

38:49.958 --> 38:52.458
In a manner befitting our shared values.

38:52.541 --> 38:55.166
-Yes.
-[quiet, overlapping murmuring]

38:57.250 --> 39:02.125
I think this conversation would benefit
from some actual ideas.

39:02.208 --> 39:04.375
Well, you know what?

39:04.458 --> 39:06.916
The young man
Woody interrogated this morning?

39:07.000 --> 39:08.791
He left an impression on me.

39:08.875 --> 39:11.416
That is the gentleman
who showed me his butthole.

39:11.500 --> 39:13.166
-[crowd gasping]
-Yes, but what I took from that

39:13.250 --> 39:15.583
is a desire to communicate.

39:15.666 --> 39:18.041
To reach out
across the cultural divide.

39:18.125 --> 39:20.500
That's a spark we can work with...

39:20.583 --> 39:22.583
to create a great citizen.

39:22.666 --> 39:25.041
Given our recently dwindled numbers,

39:25.125 --> 39:28.791
the most ethical solution would be
to rehabilitate the prisoners

39:28.875 --> 39:31.458
and then integrate them
into our Vault Society.

39:31.541 --> 39:34.000
-[indistinct, overlapping chatter]
-[microphone squeaks]

39:34.083 --> 39:38.666
[Woody] To be clear, this is not a process
that will happen overnight.

39:38.750 --> 39:40.708
Based on what I saw this morning,

39:40.791 --> 39:43.500
-it may take years.
-[crowd murmuring]

39:43.583 --> 39:45.958
-But--
-But... there is nothing

39:46.041 --> 39:48.708
we can't do
when we set our minds to it!

39:48.791 --> 39:51.416
-Yes!
-Yes!

39:52.750 --> 39:57.125
I can teach the raiders Shakespeare--
and when they're ready, Marlowe.

39:57.208 --> 39:58.791
[Marianne] I don't want to be insensitive,

39:58.875 --> 40:01.916
but I think Shakespeare might be
too advanced for these people.

40:02.000 --> 40:04.041
Look, I would like
to start with a moral framework.

40:04.125 --> 40:06.375
Kant, Mill and-and so on.

40:06.458 --> 40:08.875
I'd be happy to teach them
introductory calculus.

40:08.958 --> 40:10.333
[scoffs]

40:10.416 --> 40:12.166
[Reg] Is there something
you'd like to say,

40:12.250 --> 40:14.250
Norm?

40:16.208 --> 40:18.333
[slow, sinister music playing]

40:18.416 --> 40:20.750
I don't know. I don't think
it's our job to help these people.

40:20.833 --> 40:23.625
-They're murderers.
-They didn't know any better.

40:23.708 --> 40:25.208
[Marianne] And how could they

40:25.291 --> 40:27.500
-without a formal education?
-Norm,

40:27.583 --> 40:31.500
buddy, the hard truth is,
we can't just let them go.

40:31.583 --> 40:33.666
[laughing] Uh, it's just,

40:33.750 --> 40:36.208
they have intimate knowledge
of our Vault security.

40:36.291 --> 40:39.500
-[Steph scoffs softly]
-[Reg] So what do you propose we do?

40:41.500 --> 40:43.083
We can do
what they would have done to us.

40:43.166 --> 40:44.458
-[crowd gasping]
-Wow.

40:44.541 --> 40:45.833
Geez Louise, Norm.

40:46.875 --> 40:48.833
[Betty] Young Norm was

40:48.916 --> 40:50.916
just expressing a feeling.

40:51.000 --> 40:53.708
I know. I've got anger. We all do.

40:53.791 --> 40:55.833
But I think you would agree

40:55.916 --> 41:00.166
that murdering these prisoners of ours
is not under serious consideration.

41:00.250 --> 41:01.708
[woman] That's right.

41:01.791 --> 41:03.208
-Hear! Hear!
-[crowd murmuring]

41:03.291 --> 41:05.583
I'm sorry. You're right.

41:05.666 --> 41:08.375
It was not my intention
to question your leadership, Overseer.

41:08.458 --> 41:10.625
-Thank you.
-Thank you.
-[microphone squeaks]

41:10.708 --> 41:13.416
[engineer] All right. Sirs?

41:13.500 --> 41:15.875
Uh, sirs? Uh, uh, may I...

41:15.958 --> 41:17.208
may I speak with you for a moment, please?

41:17.291 --> 41:18.541
Uh, it's about the Water Chip.

41:18.625 --> 41:20.500
Go ahead.

41:22.500 --> 41:24.791
Uh, it's-it's... it's the type of thing

41:24.875 --> 41:27.666
Overseer MacLean would have preferred
to discuss, uh, privately?

41:27.750 --> 41:29.541
Uh, before bringing it to the full group?

41:29.625 --> 41:32.250
-[microphone squeaks]
-Well, he's not here now, is he?

41:32.333 --> 41:34.041
Let's hear it.

41:34.125 --> 41:36.291
Okay, well, uh...

41:36.375 --> 41:37.916
the Water Chip is destroyed.

41:38.000 --> 41:40.333
-[crowd clamoring]
-The Vault only has enough water to keep

41:40.416 --> 41:42.416
our population alive for, uh, two months.

41:42.500 --> 41:44.958
And-and that's not accounting
for the prisoners, who--

41:45.041 --> 41:47.541
-Okay. That's fine, that's enough.
-Thanks, though.

41:47.625 --> 41:49.250
-[Reg] Uh...
-[Woody] Um...

41:49.333 --> 41:52.375
-[crowd murmuring]
-[Reg] Okay.

41:52.458 --> 41:53.583
Uh... meeting adjourned.

41:53.666 --> 41:56.416
[Woody] I was also gonna say
meeting adjourned, so...

41:57.375 --> 41:58.708
That went well.

42:00.958 --> 42:02.958
[indistinct, overlapping chatter]

42:05.708 --> 42:07.958
They killed my husband.

42:11.708 --> 42:14.208
You're right, you know.

42:14.291 --> 42:16.166
If your father were here, he...

42:18.375 --> 42:20.791
...he'd do the right thing.

42:26.541 --> 42:29.166
[dramatic music playing]

42:38.666 --> 42:40.666
[chittering]

42:42.583 --> 42:44.500
[CX404 barking]

42:44.583 --> 42:46.291
[Maximus] [distorted] Are you sure
about this?

42:46.375 --> 42:47.666
[Thaddeus] It says the ghoul is this way.

42:47.750 --> 42:49.333
[rad meter peaking]

42:49.416 --> 42:51.416
-Wait a minute.
-What?

42:52.583 --> 42:56.291
Uh, it's just, this, um... Well, uh--

42:56.375 --> 42:58.916
-[Maximus] What?
-[Thaddeus] It just occurred to me.

43:00.208 --> 43:03.625
Uh, we're definitely picking up
an abomination of some kind or another.

43:03.708 --> 43:05.291
Just not sure...

43:05.375 --> 43:07.916
I'm not sure
we're tracking the right abomination.

43:09.291 --> 43:11.375
[loud splashing]

43:14.916 --> 43:17.250
-[Maximus] You idiot!
-It was my mistake.

43:17.333 --> 43:20.875
If you'll let me lead the charge,
I'll lead the charge.

43:22.541 --> 43:23.958
[sighs]

43:24.041 --> 43:26.375
[quietly] I am a Knight
of the Brotherhood of Steel.

43:26.458 --> 43:28.041
-Get back to shore.
-But sir--

43:28.125 --> 43:31.041
-Go!
-Thank you, sir.

43:35.750 --> 43:37.666
[soft clicking]

43:50.250 --> 43:51.833
-[growling]
-[shot fires]

43:51.916 --> 43:53.625
[questioning grunt]

43:55.208 --> 43:57.916
[growling]

43:58.000 --> 44:01.250
[♪ Glenn Miller: "In the Mood"]

44:01.333 --> 44:03.708
[low growling]

44:03.791 --> 44:05.541
[roaring]

44:07.708 --> 44:09.416
[high-pitched screaming]

44:09.500 --> 44:11.625
-[Maximus] Fuck, fuck, fuck, fuck.
-[Thaddeus yells]

44:11.708 --> 44:15.166
-My lord! [screaming]
-I've got you!

44:15.250 --> 44:16.500
Knight Titus!

44:16.583 --> 44:18.541
[growling]

44:18.625 --> 44:20.416
[high-pitched screaming]

